race.comment: TIDWELL (6) comes through a good race at Pinjarra where the form has already stacked up, and it may have already today as well in Race 1. Out in trip looks a good move for him now with the way he closed off there. Needs some luck from the draw but he looks to have struck a very winnable race. COSMIC WALTZ (5) got a long way back at Albany last start but closed off well to be 3.7L off the winner first-up. The inside draw and rise in trip are both ticks. Looks to have plenty of upside and can make his presence felt. BRAVE DRAGON (4) was a little slow to begin off a short break at Albany last time out but did close off well. Fitter for that run and Faithfull hops in the saddle, striking at 14% when teaming up with the Wolfe barn. Looks an improver. STARCHASER (9) is third-up now and rises in trip. Can see her improving sharply. MY TEA (2) flew home last start and has to be included on the back of that effort.
